From d158a729a9f0d3719943d310598e9a92df619df1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: caption-reviewer-dev <dev@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 10:11:51 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Rework layout for side-by-side comparison + box-hover
 captions

Maximize canvas space and move depth behind toggles:
  - Slim top app bar (item nav + panel toggles) and a one-line canvas
    tool strip replace the three stacked header panels.
  - Item list + folder/compare setup + filters/search move into a
    collapsible left Browse drawer; rating + Fields/Raw editor + save +
    B's reference caption move into a collapsible right Editor drawer.
    Toggle from the bar or close with Esc; both shut = full-bleed image.
  - Compare B is promoted from a cramped bottom band to an equal canvas
    column beside A; both pan/zoom/fit. A refits when B appears/leaves.
  - Hovering any box on either canvas pops a floating tooltip with that
    object's full caption (label + description + coords).

Pure layout/UX change: the editor engine, matching backend, and all
element IDs are unchanged.
---
